# Sounder – Portal 2 Sound Effects

A Portal 2 soundboard is available via `claude-notifier`. Use it to play contextual sound effects during your work by calling `claude-notifier <CATEGORY>` via Bash (async, fire-and-forget).

## When to play sounds

Play sounds **sparingly** — at most once per logical event, not on every tool call. Use `&` to run in the background so it doesn't block your work.

| Event | Category | Example trigger |
|-------|----------|-----------------|
| Build/test succeeds | `success` | After a green test run or successful build |
| Build/test fails | `error` | After a failed build or test suite |
| Repeated failures (3+) | `frustration` | Third consecutive failed attempt at something |
| Warning in output | `warning` | Compiler warnings, lint issues, deprecations |
| Task fully done | `task_complete` | When you finish a user-requested task |
| Need user input | `attention` | When you're blocked and waiting for the user |
| Something snarky fits | `sarcasm` | Optional, when the situation calls for GLaDOS commentary |
| Found what we searched for | `target` | After a successful code search or grep |
| Long task, halfway through | `encouragement` | During multi-step work to keep spirits up |

## How to call

```bash
claude-notifier error &
```

Do NOT play sounds for:
- Routine tool calls (reads, edits, greps)
- Every single commit or git operation
- When the user hasn't asked you to do anything yet